<taxonomicName id="4C3797FCD900FFFFFF1A505267E2143E" authority="Scheffrahn, Su, Mangold, 1989" authorityName="Scheffrahn, Su, Mangold" authorityYear="1989" box="[151,697,1048,1072]" class="Insecta" family="Termitidae" genus="Amitermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="5" pageNumber="586" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="floridensis" status="syn. nov.">
<emphasis id="B943306DD900FFFFFF1A5052642E143E" box="[151,373,1048,1072]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Amitermes floridensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFA6918ED900FFFFFEF6505267E2143E" author="Scheffrahn, R. H. &amp; Su, N. - Y. &amp; Mangold, J. R." box="[379,697,1048,1072]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586" pagination="618 - 625" refId="ref3982" refString="Scheffrahn, R. H., Su, N. - Y. &amp; Mangold, J. R. (1989) Amitermes floridensis, a new species and first record of a higher termite in the eastern United States (Isoptera: Termitidae: Termitinae). Florida Entomologist, 72, 618 - 625. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3495036" type="journal article" year="1989">Scheffrahn, Su, Mangold, 1989</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B943306DD900FFFFFD3250526647143E" bold="true" box="[703,796,1048,1072]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2708D16D900FFFFFD3250526647143E" box="[703,796,1048,1072]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">syn. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B88EC7FD900FFFFFF1A5014663914CE" blockId="5.[151,1436,1118,1217]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">
A key that includes the soldiers of Nearctic species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3797FCD900FFFFFD76501566281477" authorityName="Silvestri" authorityYear="1901" box="[763,883,1119,1145]" class="Insecta" family="Termitidae" genus="Amitermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="5" pageNumber="586" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B943306DD900FFFFFD76501566281477" box="[763,883,1119,1145]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Amitermes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was published by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA6918ED900FFFFFBC9501461B71476" author="Nutting, W. L." box="[1092,1260,1118,1144]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586" pagination="997 - 1032" refId="ref3678" refString="Nutting, W. L. (1990) Insecta: Isoptera. In: Dindal, D. L (Ed.), Soil Biology Guide. John Wiley &amp; Sons, New York, New York, pp. 997 - 1032." type="book chapter" year="1990">Nutting (1990)</bibRefCitation>
beginning with couplet 9a (
<taxonomicName id="4C3797FCD900FFFFFE9050C964C71492" baseAuthorityName="Desneux" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[285,412,1154,1181]" class="Insecta" family="Termitidae" genus="Amitermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="5" pageNumber="586" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wheeleri">
<emphasis id="B943306DD900FFFFFE9050C964C71492" box="[285,412,1154,1181]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">A. wheeleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). This key did not include 
<taxonomicName id="4C3797FCD900FFFFFD4250C9663F1492" authorityName="Scheffrahn, Su, Mangold" authorityYear="1989" box="[719,868,1154,1181]" class="Insecta" family="Termitidae" genus="Amitermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="5" pageNumber="586" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="floridensis">
<emphasis id="B943306DD900FFFFFD4250C9663F1492" box="[719,868,1154,1181]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">A. floridensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In order to accommodate 
<taxonomicName id="4C3797FCD900FFFFFB1B50C960601492" authorityName="Banks" authorityYear="1920" box="[1174,1339,1154,1181]" class="Insecta" family="Termitidae" genus="Amitermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="5" pageNumber="586" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="californicus">
<emphasis id="B943306DD900FFFFFB1B50C960601492" box="[1174,1339,1154,1181]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">A. californicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, couplet 9a must be modified and another couplet (10) added as follows:
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32DBFF4D900FFFFFF1A50A1614D15D9" pageId="5" pageNumber="586" type="description">
<key id="FFA6BB4ED900FFFFFF1A50A160C7159A" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">
<keyStep id="30C3F4DAD900FFFFFF1A50A160C61513" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">
<paragraph id="8B88EC7FD900FFFFFF1A50A160C7150E" blockId="5.[151,1437,1259,1428]" box="[151,1436,1259,1281]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">
<keyLead id="30C64F4AD900FFFFFF1A50A160C7150E" box="[151,1436,1259,1281]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis id="B943306DD900FFFFFF1A50A16586150F" bold="true" box="[151,221,1259,1281]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">9a (8a)</emphasis>
Teeth large, conical, directed inward.................................................................. 
<emphasis id="B943306DD900FFFFFA0950A160C7150E" bold="true" box="[1412,1436,1259,1280]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">10</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B88EC7FD900FFFFFF1A514260C61513" blockId="5.[151,1437,1259,1428]" box="[151,1437,1288,1310]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">
<keyLead id="30C64F4AD900FFFFFF1A514260C61513" box="[151,1437,1288,1310]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis id="B943306DD900FFFFFF1A514265EB1513" bold="true" box="[151,176,1288,1309]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">9b</emphasis>
Teeth acute, cut out of margin and set off from basal hump by deep notch.................................... 
<emphasis id="B943306DD900FFFFFA0B514260C61513" bold="true" box="[1414,1437,1288,1309]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">11</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30C3F4DAD900FFFFFF1A516C60C7159A" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">
<paragraph id="8B88EC7FD900FFFFFF1A516C60C71557" blockId="5.[151,1437,1259,1428]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">
<keyLead id="30C64F4AD900FFFFFF1A516C60C71557" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis id="B943306DD900FFFFFF1A516C65B21535" bold="true" box="[151,233,1317,1339]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">10a (9a)</emphasis>
Mandible blades and teeth stout, mean head width ca. 
<quantity id="4CCF419AD900FFFFFCA9516C66201535" box="[804,891,1318,1339]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.07" pageId="5" pageNumber="586" unit="mm" value="1.07">1.07 mm</quantity>
(
<figureCitation id="130CF0FAD900FFFFFC07516C615B1535" box="[906,1024,1318,1340]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1679,1703]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1655]" captionTargetId="figure-15@3.[151,1435,181,1655]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Amitermes soldier head capsules, dorsal view: A, B. A. californicus from Twenty Nine Palms, California; C, D. A. wheeleri from Corpus Christi, Texas; E, F. A. wheeleri from St. Petersburg, Florida." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480100" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480100/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Figs. 3A, B</figureCitation>
, herein); common in the arid lands of the southwestern 
<collectingCountry id="F320ACEFD900FFFFFE00510964E31556" box="[397,440,1347,1368]" name="United States of America" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">U.S.</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F320ACEFD900FFFFFE6A5109676B1557" box="[487,560,1347,1369]" name="Mexico" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Mexico</collectingCountry>
...................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C3797FCD900FFFFFB45510960C71557" authority="Banks" authorityName="Banks" authorityYear="1920" box="[1224,1436,1347,1369]" class="Insecta" family="Termitidae" genus="Amitermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="5" pageNumber="586" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="californicus">
<emphasis id="B943306DD900FFFFFB45510960001557" bold="true" box="[1224,1371,1347,1369]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">A. californicus</emphasis>
Banks
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B88EC7FD900FFFFFF1A512A60C7159A" blockId="5.[151,1437,1259,1428]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">
<keyLead id="30C64F4AD900FFFFFF1A512A60C7159A" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis id="B943306DD900FFFFFF1A512A65E7157B" bold="true" box="[151,188,1376,1397]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">10b</emphasis>
Mandible blades and teeth slender, mean head width ca. 
